Japanese Sold Net 715.6 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 
2011-05-12T00:04:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/japanese-sold-net-715-6-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended May 6 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 715.6 billion yen ($8.8 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 21.4 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 27 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 709.9 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 177.7 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 51 billion yen in stocks, and bought 242.2 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 471
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Minh Bui in Tokyo at   mbui@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  